> I am a little confused by this test. How can we guarantee that the `queryServer.shutDown()` happens before the query actually makes it to the server?

`queryServer.shutDown()` appears to be blocking call that will block until ChannelFuture completes or throws.

```
  public void shutDown() {
    try {
      _channel.close().sync();
    } catch (Exception e) {
      throw new RuntimeException(e);
    } finally {
      _workerGroup.shutdownGracefully(0, 0, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
      _bossGroup.shutdownGracefully(0, 0, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }
  }
```
